        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "(This is a Vegas character transferred over to this game. If you received this character, yay, you have extra cookies!)\n\nYour passion was always in physical perfection. As a child you fell into boxing as a way to control your hyperactivity and as a teenager you focused on it as your life's passion. As an adult you became professional, but despite your talent, one injury ended your plans. That didn't stop you. You directed your energies into promoting athletic opportunities for others. You started a series of gyms in Vegas for disadvantaged young up-and-comers to train, and that success helped you to get involved in the Las Vegas boxing association. Your passion certainly didn't hurt your wealth, but it also drew the attention of Elias/Elizabeth Romero, a Brujah who saw your drive as a potential boon for themselves, especially considering their gambling debt. They embraced you in the hopes of using your drive, influence and personal wealth to benefit them. You have had other ideas. \n\nYou've diversified in the time since your Embrace and entrenched yourself in the Vegas sports scene. You see Vegas as a first class city, worthy of first class sporting entertainment and not just the shadiness of the betting books, a place you can perfect much as you once perfected your body. You've worked to help promote the city as a venue for boxing and MMA, have pushed for clean and fair practices in the sports betting area, and most recently were one of the silent investors in the deal to get the Raiders of the NFL to Vegas. Much of this has been frowned on openly by both the Ventrue and the Toreador, who fear your direct involvement may be toeing that fine line of the Masquerade.\n\nPerhaps they had half a point. You happened to be in LA meeting with league contacts when shit went down in Vegas. Conveniently, you have a pad here in town and could crash, and you've offered sanctuary to any seeking escape - well, the ones you like anyway. Prince Petrovna has been remarkably understanding, for a fucking Ventrue, and you are just beginning to believe that there is such a thing as a Ventrue who puts sect before personal interest. The situation in Vegas has happened so quickly, you haven't been able to get your personal interests out of there yet, hell, you aren't even sure what is going on in there. You need to find out what's going on and what can be salvaged, if anything, and decide on if LA is going to be your new base of operations or not - and if Prince Petrovna can be someone you work with or just another Ventrue asshole out to use you and yours."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Sire:",
          "column_2": "Elias Romero",
          "column_3": "Reference: (If any)",
          "column_6": "Clan",
          "column_7": "Brujah - Stronger Beast"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Embrace Date:",
          "column_2": 1982,
          "column_3": "Embrace Location:",
          "column_4": "Las Vegas, NV",
          "column_6": "Generation",
          "column_7": "Neonate 11"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Who You Know",
          "column_2": "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Starting Goals",
          "column_2": "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "You have built up a life in Vegas and now you can't go back. You don't know exactly what is going down, though they are saying it's human hunters who are picking everyone off. You are laying low in LA, but want to find out what's going on there."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Vegas may have fallen, but you are safe for now. Others might be trying to get out. You can choose to help them, and if so, you can perhaps champion their cause to the court of LA for protection."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "You've always chaffed at the idea that the Ventrue have all the money and wealth and Brujah are just thugs. You may be an ex-athlete, but you aren't a thug, and can manage as well or better than most of them. LA might be a great place to prove yourself - if you can get around the Anarchs who are determined to keep showing their ass left and right."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Player Amended History",
          "column_3": "Date Submited"
        }
      ]
    },
